Description: As one of the most innovative and sought-after artists, GRAMMY Award-winning producer and DJ AFROJACK continues to push music in bold new directions. Since breaking through with the multi-platinum-selling single Take Over Control, the Dutch-born, genre-bending musician has lent his production skills to tracks and co-created major hits for artists such as Beyoncé, Pitbull, Will.i.am, and Lil Jon. He has been recognized as one of the 50 Most Important People in EDM by Rolling Stone and was featured on the Forbes 30 Under 30 music list. In 2010, he was among the first DJs to secure a Las Vegas residency, and now, 14 years later, he remains a headlining resident artist at Wynn Las Vegas. AFROJACK continues to perform worldwide at the biggest clubs and festivals while producing new music through his label, WALL Recordings, which recently completed construction of a new 800,000+ sq. ft. artist development center.

This is a man driven by an unbridled and relentless passion for music. Armin van Buuren is a born perfectionist, striving to stay on top of the scene he's helped build. As the flag-bearer of the trance movement, he's one of the most influential figures in EDM worldwide. Even though he lives an extraordinary life as one of the world's most popular DJs, he has always remained a down-to-earth guy. Armin van Buuren is constantly on the move, whether creating music in his studio or en route to his next high-end club or festival show around the globe.

Born in 1994, Almero is a French Producer living in Paris. He is now producing for 10 years and have seen his tracks released under labels like Spinnin, Protocol, Future House Music, Anjunabeats or Revealed Recordings.

Martin Garrix - the name that belongs to one of the youngest and most successful DJ's/producers championing the pop and electronic scene. Garrix has taken his expertise across the globe, by headlining festivals, breaking through territories, and collaborating with major stars including Dua Lipa, Khalid and Bono, and The Edge. Climbing yet another rung of his ladder to stardom, he is a founder of his very own label (STMPD RCRDS), owner of a studio complex in Amsterdam, and a mentor to upcoming artists.

With numerous worldwide hit singles to their name, over 500 million global streams, support from the biggest artists in the music scene and an international tour schedule that has notched up an impressive array of appearances at the world's most prestigious venues and festivals: Tomorrowland, Ultra Music Festival, Creamfields, Mysteryland, Ushuaïa and S2O to name a few: Sick Individuals continue to set new boundaries with each passing year!.

Nicky Romero has grown from a young musical prodigy to one of the most influential artists of his time. As a DJ, producer, and mogul leading the way in modern electronic dance music, Nicky is a force to be reckoned with. From iconic hits like 'Toulouse' and 'I Could Be The One' to the launch of his alias 'Monocule' in 2020, Nicky's impressive and extensive discography of originals, remixes, edits, and co-productions shows his ability to evolve with the changing world of electronic music. What stands out even more is the success and impact of his label Protocol Recordings, which he founded in 2012. Whether through new music, expanding his label, or exploring new technology, Nicky Romero always has something exciting ahead.

Moving away from city life to the English countryside to reside in a wooden lodge for a month with no social media or technological distractions, 'Take Me Away' represents Jonnie Macaire and Harry Bass (aka Third Party)'s search for that midas creative touch following a whirlwind career period which saw the duo rack up over 70 million Spotify streams on debut album 'HOPE', and follow-up 'TOGETHER', in the space of a hectic two-year span. This track marks Third Partys first original release since early 2019 and follows their widely acclaimed remix of Armin van Buuren's 'All Comes Down' last month.

Matisse & Sadko are internationally acclaimed producers and DJs comprised of siblings Aleksandr and Yury Parkhomenko. Over their illustrious career, they've made a significant impact on the electronic dance music scene. Their collaborations with renowned artists like Steve Angello, Tiësto, and Martin Garrix have led to chart-topping hits and millions of streams. The duo's journey includes founding their label, Monomark Music, and fostering a close relationship with STMPD RCRDS and Tomorrowland Music. With performances at major festivals and iconic venues worldwide, Matisse & Sadko have solidified their status as stalwarts in the realm of electronic dance music.

In 2008, three visionary artists, Steve Angello, Sebastian Ingrosso, and Axwell formed Swedish House Mafia, rewriting the rules of electronic music. They infused house music with hip-hop swagger, rock 'n' roll attitude, and cinematic grandeur. Their legendary live performances elevated dance music from clubs to arenas and stadiums. They made history headlining Madison Square Garden in 2011 and headlining Coachella with The Weeknd in 2022, even partnering with Ikea to extend their unique aesthetic to a broader audience.
